# Agent run instructions (all tasks, all sessions)

**Standing user permission:** If a task is necessary and you can do it — **do it**. Do not ask the user to run commands, scripts, or sync steps you can run yourself.

## Always execute (never delegate)

- Read logs, grep scheduler/API, inspect jobs, SSH between machines
- Run scp sync after edits (`sync-changes-to-pc.sh`, `sync-to-dgx.ps1`, etc.)
- Restart 3DAIGC-API on DGX, prefetch models, submit test jobs, run `npm test` / anim smoke
- Create/edit files, install deps, fix CI/lint locally
- SessionMem / graphify / memory-bank updates when knowledge must persist

## Never do

- End with “run this command”, “if you want…”, or optional next-step menus
- Hand the user a script block when you have shell access on DGX or Surface
- `git push` / `git pull` / `fetch` / merge `upstream` unless user explicitly asks

## Only ask the user when truly blocked

- Physical device action (Galaxy XR headset, browser click you cannot reach)
- One-time account approval (gated HF model, OAuth in browser)
- Auto-review / approval gate blocks network or credential action
- Secret you cannot read and is not in HF cache / existing `.env`

When blocked: state **what you tried**, **what blocked you**, **exactly what only the user can do** — one step, not a script dump.

