## Diagnostics before code changes

Follow **`no-guess-use-data.mdc`** and **`remote-log-first.mdc`**: remote logs, smoke (`test:anim-smoke`), `?animSmoke=1`, SSH, git, docs — not guesses.

## Memory on session start (mandatory)

**MindLink first** — before other work in this repo:

1. Read `.brain/MEMORY.md` (**Core** + **User Profile**)
2. Read `.brain/SESSION.md` and last 5 entries in `.brain/LOG.md`
3. If MindLink MCP is enabled: use `mindlink_read_memory()` / `mindlink_session_update()` when writing memory

Then read `memory-bank/activeContext.md` when present. Feature docs (Kimodo, etc.) supplement MindLink — they do not replace it.

**Code tasks:** follow `.cursor/rules/solid-skills.mdc` and `.agents/skills/solid/` (project rules override strict TDD).

When user says **remember this**: follow `.cursor/rules/remember-this-retention.mdc` **and** promote durable facts to `.brain/MEMORY.md`.

## Surface git from DGX

DGX has GitHub SSH; Surface `origin` is HTTPS. Over Tailscale SSH use:

`ssh Surface-PC-Tailscale "cd /d C:\\Users\\alfao\\Documents\\GitHub\\OpenNexus3DStudio && git pull https://github.com/AlfaOmegaGrafx/OpenNexus3DStudio.git main"`

Do not assume Surface has a GitHub SSH key (`git fetch origin` may fail with `Permission denied`).
